
[1]hotbed

   HOT'BED, n. In gardening, a bed of earth and horsedung or tanner's
   bark, covered with glass to defend it form the cold air, intended for
   raising early plants, or for nourishing exotic plants of warm climates,
   which will not thrive in cool or temperate air.
